03e0dce4-d462-448c-9fab-ab42713208da	Q2 2026\r\n\r\n# US Evergreen Fund Landscape\r\n\r\nPitchBook clients can access this report and its Excel data pack via the Research Center on the PitchBook Platform.\r\n\r\n### The evergreen fund redemption wave was always coming [...] ### The evergreen fund redemption wave was always coming\r\n\r\nRedemptions were the story of the quarter for evergreen funds. After years of money flowing only one way, investors began pulling capital out. Outflows were concentrated mostly in private credit funds, as investors, driven by fears about loans to software companies in an AI-shaken market, pulled capital. Our reading is calmer than the headlines. The caps that limit quarterly withdrawals are working as designed. Research from our Morningstar colleagues drives the point home: Using actively managed mutual funds and ETFs as examples of vehicles that allow investors to exit, acute outflows are inevitable in a fund’s life cycle. Evergreen funds are simply getting their first real stress test. [...] The US evergreen universe now tops $600 billion, with our data extending to non-40-Act fund structures. The broad evergreen index (Morningstar PitchBook US Evergreen Fund Index) gained 1.6% through April, compared to roughly 7% posted in each of the past two calendar years, with performance being held down so far by the index’s large weighting in direct lending. Our suite of evergreen indexes is a useful high-frequency gauge that allows us to cross-check whether outflows are being matched by performance pressures.\r\n\r\nTable of contents\r\n\r\n|  |  |\r\n --- |\r\n| Market overview | 3 |\r\n| Assets and flows | 5 |\r\n| Performance | 8 |\r\n| Spotlight: Outflows are inevitable | 11 |\r\n| Fees and terms | 15 |\r\n| Fund ratings | 17 |\r\n| Notable funds | 19 |\r\n| Appendix: Glossary | 22 |	{"title": "Q2 2026 US Evergreen Fund Landscape - PitchBook", "format": "web", "source": "https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q2-2026-us-evergreen-fund-landscape", "fetch_time": "1784022709312", "source_url": "https://pitchbook.com/news/reports/q2-2026-us-evergreen-fund-landscape", "chunk_index": 0, "source_type": "web", "total_chunks": 1, "published_date": "Tue, 07 Jul 2026 22:42:12 GMT", "parent_document_id": "f7c372f7-fed1-40cd-95af-e4a30e501899"}	[-0.07237937,-0.03921373,-0.049491517,-0.019260976,-0.064354785,-0.06150863,0.00848412,0.065540686,-0.0013464895,0.06621269,0.004345826,0.025872363,-0.023401741,0.017363539,0.03377836,-0.08459413,0.025398003,0.029370766,-0.04889857,-0.035833914,0.009655194,0.023816805,0.041585524,0.015169625,-0.042099416,0.10854929,-0.07269561,-0.031386793,-0.03779065,0.016543292,0.04573617,0.04625006,0.02312503,0.021464773,-0.0071302177,0.011602045,-0.010208614,-0.04037986,-0.08878431,-0.025398003,-0.030003246,0.02018993,-0.010791681,-0.038126655,0.06083662,-0.08087831,0.008706476,-0.03668381,-0.017314125,0.010663209,-0.017660012,0.00040610865,0.042020354,-0.038996313,0.023421505,-0.008385294,-0.052298147,0.055381484,0.017561188,-0.06123192,-0.015416687,-0.0035601677,-0.0646315,0.012955947,0.024291165,0.07150971,0.03723723,-0.0065224445,-0.020456757,0.026010718,-0.020674173,-0.011048626,-0.044392154,-0.021247357,-0.054076996,0.0028585107,0.004437239,-0.03644663,0.03081361,0.010010964,0.09763902,-0.08372447,-0.03399577,0.0126990015,-0.038126655,0.01895462,0.031386793,0.027196618,0.038205713,-0.0062309112,-0.025990954,-0.036584985,0.02018993,-0.027552387,-0.040755395,0.027987218,-0.054669943,0.025773538,0.0035231083,0.018094843,0.049610108,-0.018144256,-0.033244703,-0.017660012,0.009091892,-0.014428438,0.05115178,0.044826984,0.019626629,-0.027058262,0.008790476,0.053523574,0.030042775,0.039569497,-0.025398003,-0.010524854,0.014458085,-0.0066805645,0.036624514,-0.009314248,-0.0059196125,0.015219037,0.04763361,0.036189687,0.02533871,-0.08830994,0.055460542,0.03470731,0.0088053,0.017946605,-0.010969566,0.025061999,-0.07052146,0.00084248243,-0.07455352,-0.011078273,-0.0038146419,-0.00829141,-0.