513ac1d2-9612-4fba-aedd-c3618b1b4664	Image 41: CD Rates Today: July 6, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: July 6, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% Image 42: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 43: CD Rates Today: July 2, 2026 – Rates As High As 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: July 2, 2026 – Rates As High As 4.94% Image 44: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 45: CD Rates Today: July 1, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: July 1, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% Image 46: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 47: CD Rates Today: June 30, 2026 – Earn As Much As 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: June 30, 2026 – Earn As Much As 4.94% Image 48: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger [...] 2-year CD rates:If you can hold out for two years, 2-year CDs today are being offered at interest rates as high as 4.35%. The top rate last week was 4.25%. The average APY for this CD term is 1.63%, flat to last week's average.\r\n   3-year CD rates:Today's highest rate on a three-year CD is 4.17%, so you'll want to shop around for that rate or something near it. The average APY stands at 1.55%.\r\n   5-year CD rates:The highest rate available today for a five-year CD is 4.26%. The average APY is 1.57%,similar to last week. [...] 3-month CD rates:These are a good option for short-term savings goals. The current averageannual percentage yield (APY)on a three-month CD sits at 1.19%, but the highest rate is 4.38%. The average rate is unchanged from a week ago.\r\n   6-month CD rates:These offer a nice blend of high yields and short-term time commitment, and the highest yield you can find is 4.94%, about the same as last week.	{"title": "CD Rates Today: July 8, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% - Forbes", "format": "web", "source": "https://www.forbes.com/advisor/banking/cds/cd-rates-today-07-08-26/", "fetch_time": "1784029875679", "source_url": "https://www.forbes.com/advisor/banking/cds/cd-rates-today-07-08-26/", "chunk_index": 0, "source_