fe9737ff-d0de-4cc1-94b0-80a59b103bc7	Image 45: CD Rates Today: July 6, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: July 6, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% Image 46: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 47: CD Rates Today: July 2, 2026 – Rates As High As 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: July 2, 2026 – Rates As High As 4.94% Image 48: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 49: CD Rates Today: July 1, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% ##### CD Rates Today: July 1, 2026 – Take Home Up To 4.94% Image 50: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger [...] 2-year CD rates:If you can hold out for two years, 24-month CDs today are being offered at interest rates as high as 4.35%. That's the same as this time last week. The average APY for this CD term is 1.63%, flat to last week's average.\r\n   3-year CD rates:Today, the highest rate on a three-year CD stands at 4.20%, so you'll want to shop around for that rate or something near it. The average APY is 1.55%.\r\n   5-year CD rates:On a five-year CD, the highest rate today is 4.26%. APYs are averaging 1.58%, similar to last week. [...] on a three-month CD sits at 1.19%, but the highest rate is 4.38%. The average rate is unchanged from a week ago.\r\n   6-month CD rates:These offer a nice blend of high yields and short-term time commitment, and the highest yield you can find is 4.94%, about the same as last week. The current average APY for a six-month CD is 1.61%.\r\n   1-year CD rates:The highest interest rate currently available on a 12-month CD—one of the most popular CD terms—is 4.84%. If you discover a rate in that neighborhood, you're getting a good deal. That rate hasn't changed much since last week. The average APY on a one-year CD is now 1.81%, unchanged from a week ago.	{"title": "CD Rates Today: July 10, 2026 – Earn As Much As 4.94% - Forbes", "format": "web", "source": "https://www.forbes.com/advisor/banking/cds/copy-of-cd-rates-today-07-10-26/", "fetch_time": "1784029876185", "source_url": "https://