22c31638-391b-4dbc-a28f-e671b5a02f70	Image 43: High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 6, 2026 – Rates Are Steady ##### High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 6, 2026 – Rates Are Steady Image 44: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 45: High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 2, 2026 – Rates Are Steady ##### High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 2, 2026 – Rates Are Steady Image 46: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger\r\n\r\nImage 47: High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 1, 2026 – Rates Are Steady ##### High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 1, 2026 – Rates Are Steady Image 48: Michael BenningerBy Michael Benninger [...] On high-yield accounts requiring a minimum deposit of $25,000, the highest available rate today is 3.93%.You’ll be in good shape if you can get an account offering a rate close to that.That’s about the same as one week ago.\r\n\r\nThe current average APY for those accounts is now 0.23%, unchanged from a week ago.\r\n\r\n## National Average Savings Account Yields\r\n\r\nHere’s an overview of how the national average APY on savings accounts has changed over the past few years.\r\n\r\n## This Week’s Best High-Yield Savings Accounts\r\n\r\nHere’s an overview of the current APYs available from some of today’s best high-yield savings accounts.\r\n\r\n## How Often Do Savings Account Interest Rates Change? [...] Subscribe To Newsletters\r\n\r\n for a traditional savings account is 0.22%,Curinos says. APY reflects the actual return your account will earn during one year. It accounts for compound interest, which is the interest that accrues on the interest in your account.\r\n\r\n## High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today\r\n\r\nHigh-yield savings accountsgenerally pay much more interest than conventional savings accounts. But the trade-off is you may have to jump through some hoops to earn that higher rate, such as becoming a member of acredit unionor putting down a large deposit.\r\n\r\nOn high-yield accounts requiring a minimum deposit of $10,000, today’s best interest rate is 4.16%.That’s about the same as one week ago.\r\n\r\nThe average APY for those accounts is now 0.22%, unchanged from a week ago.	{"title": "High-Yield Savings Account Rates Today: July 8, 2026 – Rates Are Steady - Forbes", "format": "web", "source": "https://www.forbes.com/advisor/banking/savings/savings-account-rates-today-07-08-26/", "fetch_time": "1784029877368", "source_url": "https://www.forbes.com/advisor/banking/savings/savings-account-rates-today-07-08-26/", "chunk_index": 0, "source_type": "web", "total_chunks": 1, "published_date": "Wed, 08 Jul 2026 07:13:37 GMT", "parent_document_id": "a34face8-77b2-4abe-8ff2-8a6684b6f7a7"}	[-0.030990817,-0.017524345,-0.04567465,-0.018741706,-0.026574342,-0.05228049,0.010899632,0.072852954,0.0040838234,-0.0042843577,0.04952491,0.022138994,-0.064170994,0.021157555,0.0022624994,-0.012560529,0.017798014,0.03327455,-0.0432588,-0.047260053,-0.006025468,0.03140604,0.03535067,-0.01323055,0.029122308,0.047411043,-0.119056076,0.012730394,0.042277362,0.021535031,0.0126360245,0.03993701,0.058206867,-0.032462973,0.01900594,0.018798327,-0.025158806,-0.014400726,-0.06609613,0.028631588,0.032915946,-0.014334668,-0.0085026575,0.03116068,0.09014138,-0.022044625,0.0038148714,-0.020402603,-0.010795826,-0.011758392,-0.009177396,-0.013702395,0.049977884,-0.058206867,0.050770584,-0.0017340324,0.020968817,0.016844887,-0.047222305,-0.02957528,-0.0076344614,0.03382189,-0.051034816,0.02557403,0.02068571,-0.0063321674,0.0028310735,0.047524285,-0.06828549,-0.016571216,-0.0005443918,0.019166367,0.009191551,0.002514937,-0.056281738,0.020761205,0.015485971,0.0042300955,0.0064076628,-0.04137142,0.067757025,-0.048279237,0.048920948,0.02789551,-0.036954943,0.08251635,0.027631275,0.07277746,0.037691023,-0.024233988,-0.008516813,-0.034595717,0.040805206,-0.0158257,-0.0044707367,0.022044625,-0.04261709,0.030934196,0.0004234814,0.0072758584,0.045297176,0.019100308,-0.0064265365,-0.0344447