d74b3e72-578f-4dbf-a9c3-144719241a42	Changjiang Communication Co., Ltd. (600345.SH) announced that on February 13 and March 6, 2026, the company’s board approved authorizing management to opportunistically sell up to 1 million A-shares of Yangtze Optical Fibre & Cable Co., Ltd. As of July 9, 2026, the company had sold 999,985 A-shares of Yangtze Optical Fibre & Cable via centralized bidding transactions, generating proceeds of RMB 4.12 billion at prices ranging from RMB 380.03 to RMB 448.02 per share. Following this transaction, the company continues to hold 118 million shares of Yangtze Optical Fibre & Cable, representing 14.23% of its total share capital. The impact of this share sale on the company’s 2026 profit before tax is estimated at approximately RMB 3.76 billion (excluding income tax effects). [...] [Taiji Industry: Wuxi High-tech Investment, an acting-in-concert party of the controlling shareholder, reduced its stake by 2.3% on July 9]\n\nTaiji Industry Co., Ltd. (600667.SH) announced that Wuxi High-tech Investment, an acting-in-concert party of the company’s controlling shareholder, reduced its holdings by a total of 48 million shares (representing 2.3% of the company’s total share capital) through centralized bidding and block trades on July 9, 2026. As a result, the combined stake held by the controlling shareholder and its acting-in-concert parties decreased from 33.52% to 31.22%, triggering a 1% threshold disclosure requirement for equity changes. This reduction was not part of any pre-disclosed plan and will not result in a change of control or actual controller of the company. [...] [Meichang Shares: H1 Net Profit Expected to Increase by 248%–272% Year-over-Year; Tungsten Wire Diamond Wire Sales Mix Improves]\n\nMeichang Shares (300861.SZ) announced that it expects net profit attributable to shareholders of the listed company for the first half of 2026 to be RMB 295 million–RMB 315 million, representing a year-over-year increase of 248.45%–272.08%.